Skip to Content   Skip to Search   Skip to Navigation   Skip to Sub Navigation                                                             New York University College of Dentistry                                   Search NYUCD                                                                                                                       Main Navigation                                       About                                                                       Admissions/Academic Programs                                                            Departments/Faculty                                              Research                                              Student Life                                              Alumni                                              CDE                                              Global Reach                                              Patients                                              Admissions/Academic Programs             Programs for International Dentists                                                                                          The Programs for International Dentists at NYU College of Dentistry attracts oral health professionals from over 89 countries. These full-time programs are designed for international dentists who plan to practice dentistry outside the United States. Completion of any of these programs does not qualify participants for licensure in the US.   CLINICAL PROGRAMS   The programs offer a curriculum of didactic components and clinical experiences in the following disciplines: Comprehensive Dentistry , Endodontics , Esthetic Dentistry , Implant Dentistry , Oral Medicine & Orofacial Pain, Oral Surgery , Oral Surgery/RCSI , Orthodontics , Periodontics and Prosthodontics . Programs vary from one-, two- and three-years in length, with opportunities to participate in elective experiences such as teaching, research and society meetings. In addition, certain programs offer the opportunity for students to participate in NYUCD’s Global Outreach Program .   Teaching and Research Fellowship Programs   The Consortium for Translational Orthodontic Research (CTOR) program offers a one- or two-year program with an open environment within which basic scientists and clinicians can interact, exchange ideas, select and pursue research in specific areas of Craniofacial Biology and Orthodontics.The Teaching in Dental Education (TIDE) Fellowship is a one-year, full-time course of study designed to foster the career development of dental educators.        2015 Summer Program   The 2015 Summer Practicum for International Dental Students at New York University College of Dentistry is designed for international dental students from universities outside the US who are interested in gaining a US dental education experience with exposure to New York City culture. Skip to Content   Skip to Search   Skip to Navigation   Skip to Sub Navigation                                                             New York University College of Dentistry                                   Search NYUCD                                                                                                                       Main Navigation                                       About                                              Admissions/Academic Programs                                              Departments/Faculty                                              Research                                              Student Life                                              Alumni                                                                       CDE                                                            Global Reach                                              Patients                                               CDE > US Clinical Participation            Implantology                              upcoming continuing education events                                         go to calendar                                                                                                     Surgical and Prosthetic Treatment   This comprehensive, multi-disciplinary course will meet approximately 60 sessions over a two-year period. Participants can expect to complete surgical and prosthetic treatment on four patients. Patients are provided by New York University College of Dentistry. To register for this program, please call Jarett J. Gilbert, Director, at (212) 998-9757.   What you'll learn:          Textbook & Literature Review   Case Presentations   Diagnosis & Patient Work-up with Experienced Faculty            Treatment Planning Utilizing Advanced CT Software   Non-traumatic Extractions   Socket Preservation Grafting            Implant Placement & 2nd Stage Surgeries   Guided Tissue Regeneration   Fixed & Removable Implant Prosthetics           Two-Year Program: September 2014 - June 2016   Participants will be assigned to one of the following sessions:        Session I  Session II  Session III  Session IV  Session V        Monday  Monday  Wednesday  Wednesday  Thursday        8:30 am - 1:15 pm  11:45 am - 4:30 pm  8:30 am - 1:15 pm  11:45 am - 4:30 pm  8:30 am - 1:15 pm         Program Director     Dr. Trevor Bavar   ASSOCIATE DIRECTORS   Dr. Spyridon Condos (Monday)  Dr. Robert Bagoff (Wednesday)  Dr. Robert Friedman and Dr. David Kim (Thursday)                                                     Click flyer above to learn more and complete the Registration Form, which has fillable fields. Form must be downloaded (ie, saved on your computer), then opened with Adobe Acrobat. After filling in fields electronically on the downloaded file, select "File > Send" and email the completed form to dentalcde@nyu.edu. Visit www.adobe.com to learn more about Adobe products.
